cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.CY, cs.CR, cs.SI

The paper discusses the limitations of using journal rank as a scientific impact assessment tool, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a library-based scholarly communication system. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of modern information technology to improve the filter, sort, and discovery functions of the current journal system. cs.CY (Computers and Society) is relevant as the paper discusses the negative impact of institutionalizing journal rank. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) are less likely but still possible as the paper touches on the methodological soundness and expert ratings of scientific quality.
